metadata.name: Honest Grind
metadata.description:
I was lost in a crowd. Varanasi is a maze of smoky alleyways, lined with incense and dusky pink temples. As I emerge onto the banks of the Ganges, I see a hawker. Her expression lies in contrast to her garment.

A pilgrim approaches her to buy some of her fragranced flowers. As the customers walks away, the hawker notices a flower has split onto the floor. She jostles through the crowd and returns it to the customer, and they exchange a smile.

In a land where corruption and dishonesty are not uncommon, there are those who still value an honest day's work.

Pentax P30 + SMC 50mm f/1.7, Portra 400.
Varanasi, India.
March 2018.
